public class ListChooserPanel
extends javax.swing.JPanel

ListChooserPanel is intended to be used within a dialog. The dialog is to be known by this panel, so that it can be turned off by the panel. It is used to present the user with choices, in a list. Only one item can be chosen. Clicking OK changes the offical chosen value to the one the user chose. Clicking Cancel will make it the original value. It was designed for use with ThreepioFrame, but can be used for anything.

Author:
Jhoule
